Anonymous Mon 03 Jun 2024 16:20:37 No.66294686 Report
Quoted By: >>66294824 >>66294829 >>66296613
>>66294320
Writing advice from an elder:

Do not make a "slow burn" or "slow buildup" story if you're trying to get into writing, even if it's a return. That is the worst idea possible. You might have a lot of momentum right away, but after a year or two most writers burn out on their own stories. Whatever you make, keep the idea and scope fairly simple or constrained. Having a word or page limit so that you're accountable to something while writing is useful as well.
The next worst idea is outsource your motivation to popular appeal. Brainstorm if you need it, but you need to learn to make all these decisions instead of offloading. There's an audience for nearly everything, and if you fail then that's a learning experience.
